Author::::angdavies
DateTime::::2016-03-11T14:25:47Z
What Mr Lott is missing in his observations is the massive societal transition from collectivism to individualism that started in the late seventies. Although acceptance of individualism - often in tandem with levels of narcissism - has led to a far more tolerant society, we have also lost much of our ability to unify for a collective good . Pretty much all the social taboos that can be legal have been accepted as mainstream. I presume there is nostalgia from people that really had to fight for their right to be different before the eighties, and who feel somewhat peeved that a form of social trangression as powerful as visible tattooing, that literally used to mark you out, and often proscribed your life chances, is now just an everyday fashion accessory.



